title: For Sale:  1916 Berthier Rifle
postcontent: For sale is a Model 1916 bolt action rifle from Fusile (Berthier). This Berthier rifle has a 32" barrel and is chambered in 8mm Lebel. This French Lebel rifle is fed by a 5-round enbloc clip (one included) and is in good condition for a rifle of its age. The bluing is aged and has minor surface pitting. The wood stock is heavily worn (the French beat these things up over the decades) yet the action is smooth and the base plate swings open easily. The bore is in good condition with clear rifling grooves. All serial numbers match on bolt, bolt head, trigger guard, and butt stock. "N" stamped on both barrel and receiver. These are hard to find in the US and there are no import markings. A great gun for anyone interested in World War One weapons or military history. US African American troops under French command would've had opportunity to use this arm along with its three-shot predecessor. More pictures available upon request. Must have SC license for local sale.

title: For Sale:  Sig 556/551A1 Patrol Carbine
postcontent: This one is a custom built rifle that has a Sig 556 Patrol Carbine with a 16" melonite coated barrel mated to a Sig Sauer factory 551A1 lower. It has the excellent MFI 553 type handguards installed and the MFI 3 prong 553 type flash suppressor. The front sight is the factory Sig Hooded front sight and the receiver mounted rail has a flip-up rear sight. A Sig Sauer rotary diopter sight has been added which offers a combat V notch and 3 diopter positions for 100-200-300 meters. It is a HK type rotary drum and they are extremely easy to use once you get them dialed in.   These 556 rifles are no longer in production and are highly sought by collectors and shooters. They are an interesting design and many have referred to them as product improved AK designs.   The Magazine is a hard to find 20-rd 551 type that was offered by Sig-USA years ago. The 551A1 lower accepts all 550/551 type magazines.  This carbine weighs a trim 7.5lbs as shown with the magazine. It handles extremely well and shoulders comfortably and the folding Swiss Type 556 stock offers a surprisingly comfortable cheek weld. It is a very tight feeling rifle due to to the shorter stock, almost AK-like in length which makes it very fast to track onto target.  This is not a Sig factory combination and is a custom rifle that apporximates the Sig 553 carbine very nicely with the exception of the longer barrel.   This 556/551A1 Carbine is available for sale. Shipping is included in the asking price (Valued at $45.00 for fully insured and positive signature delivery)Additional photos on our Facebook Page:  Sig 556-551A1 Patrol
